n the level of help you need. </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Rate</th>\n      <th>Level of help you need</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Lower rate - £51.85</td>\n      <td>Frequent help or constant supervision during the day, or supervision at night</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Higher rate - £77.45</td>\n      <td>Help or supervision throughout both day and night, or you’re terminally ill</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances are paid <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"how to have your benefits paid\">into an account</a>, eg your bank account.</p>\n\n<h2>Changes of circumstances</h2>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s your responsibility to tell the helpline if your circumstances change, as this can affect how much you get. For example, you or the person you claim for needs more help, goes into hospital or moves abroad. </p>\n\n<p>Usually your Attendance Allowance won&rsquo;t be affected if you go: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>into hospital or a care home for less than 4 weeks </li>\n  <li>abroad for less than 26 weeks </li>\n  <li>abroad to get medical treatment for a condition which began before you left </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You could get extra Pension Credit, Housing Benefit or Council Tax Benefit if you get Attendance Allowance - check with the helpline or office dealing with your benefit.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Disability Benefits Helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 08457 123 456<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 08457 224 433  <br />\n Monday to Friday, 8am to 6pm</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/attendance-allowance/eligibility","slug":"eligibility","order":3,"title":"Eligibility","body":"<p>You can get Attendance Allowance if you&rsquo;re 65 or over and the following apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you have a physical disability (including 