ts). You might qualify for one or both components. </p>\n\n<h2>Care component</h2>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Care component</th>\n      <th>Weekly rate</th>\n      <th>Level of help you need</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Lowest</td>\n      <td>£20.55</td>\n      <td>Help for some of the day or with preparing cooked meals</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Middle</td>\n      <td>£51.85</td>\n      <td>Frequent help or constant supervision during the day, supervision at night or someone to help you while on dialysis</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Highest</td>\n      <td>£77.45</td>\n      <td>Help or supervision throughout both day and night, or you&rsquo;re terminally ill</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Mobility component</h2>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Mobility component</th>\n      <th>Weekly rate</th>\n      <th>Level of help you need</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Lower</td>\n      <td>£20.55</td>\n      <td>Guidance or supervision outdoors</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Higher</td>\n      <td>£54.05</td>\n      <td>You have any other, more severe, walking difficulty</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>How you&rsquo;re paid</h2>\n\n<p>All benefits, pensions and allowances are paid <a href=\"/how-to-have-your-benefits-paid\" title=\"how to have your benefits paid\">into an account</a>, eg your bank account.</p>\n\n<h2>Change of circumstance</h2>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s your responsibility to tell the helpline if your circumstances change - this can affect how much you get. For example, your disability gets worse or you go for medical treatment abroad.</p>\n\n<p>Usually your <abbr title=\"Disability Living Allowance\">DLA</abbr> won&rsquo;t be affected if you: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>go into hospital or a care home for less than 4 weeks (or 12 weeks if you&rsquo;re a under 16) </li>\n  <li>go abroad for less than 26 weeks </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\